\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 101.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 In our Act, the failing firm doctrine is not used as a \'91defence\'92 to a merger that has been found on an initial market analysis to be anticompetitive. Rather it is recognised as one of list of \'91factors\'92 that one takes into account before one can determine w
hether a merger is anti-competitive. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx360{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 102.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 Thus in some jurisdictions, such as the United States, the adjudicator would first determine whether a merger was anti-competitive and then only if it was, consider the failing firm doctrine as a defence. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx360{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 103.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 Our Act does not divide the inquiry into two discrete stages. The way section 12A(2) is drafted, the consideration of whether a merger is anti-competitive involves as part of that inquiry a consideration of a non-exhaustive list of factors, one of which is
 whether a party to the merger is a failing firm. In contrast to this, our \'91efficiency defence\'92{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s14\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs33\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0 The phrase \'91efficiency defence\'92 is just a convenient shorthand for the defence that the merger can be justified on account of any \'91technological, efficiency or other pro-competitive gain\'92 that would offset any anti-competitive effect of the merger and that
 would not likely be obtained absent the merger. (See section 12 A (1)(a)(i) ).}}}
{\*\cs33\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af9\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } is a real defence to an anti-competitive merger and for this reason is located in a self-standing sub-paragraph of section 12A, as a reading of section 12A(1)(
a)(i) makes clear. To invoke the efficiency defence one first has to conclude that the merger is anti-competitive. This one does by first conducting the inquiry into the factors contained in section 12A(2). Then, and only if that inquiry leads to the concl
usion that the merger is anti-competitive, does one go on to enquire whether the efficiencies gained outweigh the anti-competitive effects.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 104.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 The distinction might appear to be a mere lawyers quibble with no practical significance, but this is not so. If the failing firm doctrine was a \'93true defence\'94, then if all the elements of the defence could be established, an anti-competitive merger would 
have to be approved. However if it is just one of a list of factors to be taken into account, in the list set out in section 12A(2), then even if it was established, that the firm was failing, by say the application of the US or EU tests, one might neverth
eless still find a merger to be anti-competitive because of the way one balances this failing firm factor in relation to all the others. It is thus possible in terms of the Act, that a credible failing firm theory may nevertheless not save a merger, which 
raises serious competition concerns. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 105.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 Conversely, where the competitive loss is low, then one may be less exacting in requiring a showing of all the elements of the traditional failing firm defence. If the failing firm concept was a defence, in the sense that the efficiency defence is, then th
is type of flexibility would be impermissible and one would have to satisfy all the elements of a test that the legislature had provided before it could be invoked.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\cf5\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 106.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s3\cf5\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0 Whilst this approach may risk making the concept more nebulous, it does allow the adjudicator the flexibility to achieve real interest balancing, as opposed to the application of rigid formulas.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s3\cf5\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li-360\ri0\lin-360\rin0\fi60\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\cf3\f8\f4\fs24\f4\lang1025\qj\tx540 107.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s3\cf3\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls0\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af4\langfe255\hich\f8\fs24\lang7177\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f8\fs24\lang7177\i0\b0{\cf5 A flexible approach, allows one for instance to have regard to some of the rationale for the failing firm defence even though they do not constitute elements of a traditional defence. Thus if one rationale, as Areeda puts it, is to avoid inhibiting investm
